description:
I met and became good friends with Betty Carter in 1975 while she was appearing at "The Empty Foxhole Cafe" in Philadelphia. In 1980, I produced a documentary on the career of Betty Carter which also included filming her concert performance for Philadelphia station WPVI-TV. During a 1989 segment on my "Bebop City" program titled "The Bebop Singers", Betty Carter told me this incredible story about her early career and the Lionel Hampton Orchestra. 

It was my great pleasure to have Betty Carter as a music family friend. It is with this hope that young Jazz Vocalists will take some instruction from a master vocal teacher who can help you find your own original style.

DR. BOP
